content: We consulted the experts, and there's only one thing left to do for our 9th birthday. #ThankYou

author: Twitter
content: 9/9: We're amazed at how far we've traveled together. #ThankYou for an incredible nine years.

author: Twitter
content: 8/9: And we continue to be captivated by what you create and Tweet every day.

author: Twitter
content: 7/9: Over the years, you've shared what you care about with people around the world.

author: Twitter
content: 6/9: Together, we followed those moments as they turned into movements.

author: Twitter
content: 5/9: As people shared what was happening in the moment, the world watched breaking news unfold in real time.

author: Twitter
content: 4/9: Adding to our global community, world leaders also joined the conversation.

author: Twitter
content: 3/9: And Twitter became a place for all kinds of voices, big and small.

author: Twitter
content: 2/9: Right away, you began giving us great ideas to help make Twitter better.

author: Twitter
content: 1/9: Nine years ago, it all started with a Tweet.

content: In Col with our schools we’ve seen crime rates drop & gangs disband. Kids who'd have been recruited are on the way to univ. #ShakiraEdChat

content: Preschool costs ~ $8k per year per child. Juvenile detention costs ~ $90k per year per child. Again-numbers don’t lie. #ShakiraEdChat

content: #ShakiraEdChat It’s key to have comprehensive programs, teacher training, AND work with the parents to work in challenging environments

author: shakira
content: .@isaura_cd De 0 a 3, todos los niños son genios lingüísticos por su plasticidad cerebral. A través de los idiomas enseñamos la globalidad

author: shakira
content: .@Its_Pema poverty is perpetuated by the lack of opportunities like universal access to quality ed. Education is a birthright-not a luxury

author: shakira
content: .@keithdhardy spending time with their kids, sending them to school early, giving them nutrition, stimulation and love

author: shakira
content: .@Tayosaid Porqué he visto los milagros que logra en niños, familias, y comunidades enteras en Colombia y en otros países donde trabajamos

author: shakira
content: .@ShakNewsQuilla Cualquier niño puede aprender idiomas antes de los 3-a Milan lo exponemos al esp, catalán, ing, francés, aleman, ruso,chino

author: shakira
content: .@SHAKITINILOCA teaching them that education is an equalizer that gives us all the same chances no matter what conditions we’re born into

author: shakira
content: Agree! RT @arneduncan .@FeimM Please challenge all political leaders to invest in high quality learning opportunities for children 0-5.

author: shakira
content: .@saleosol education turns kids into productive citizens, is proven to boost GDPs of nations, and promotes global security and stability.

author: shakira
content: .@PreschoolNation Chile's model increased funds for ECD & schools , virtually eliminated illiteracy & drastically improved teacher training

author: shakira
content: .@KnowledgeAll Fund. pies descalzos es parte de una alianza con el gob. Nal. "Primero lo primero". Abriremos 24 centros de DIT para 2016!

author: shakira
content: .@DJRarela showing leaders how early ed gives back & sharing success stories of transformed communities strengthens the case for investing

author: shakira
content: .@Anna_Isabel05 kids are able 2 comprehend more than we think-It’s never too early 2 start teaching&exposing them to books even as newborns

author: shakira
content: .@theonlywayisjam growing up surrounded by inequality made me intolerant to it, & research showed me that education was the solution to it

author: shakira
content: .@ShakiraQuilla hemos aprendido que se debe educar desde los inicios para poder solventar los desafíos que se encuentran mas adelante

author: shakira
content: .@Mellisebasan de acuerdo. faltan mas escuelas en los campos, mas compromisos de los gobiernos y el sector privado. Hay que presionar

author: shakira
content: .@stumpteacher babies have an innate thirst for knowledge and enjoy learning-making it fun through focused play is another way of bonding.

author: shakira
content: .@CO7649 Every $1 invested in early ed for disadvantaged kids has a return of at least 10% & reduces social spending. Numbers don’t lie!

author: shakira
content: .@JoseRendon0 In ECD, bc kids who access it are better prepared to learn through primary, secondary & higher ed, and thrive throughout life

author: shakira
content: .@keithdhardy unequal access to ed. affects nations rich & poor, but in the US school dropouts will be reduced by increasing ECD programs

author: shakira
content: .@cynthiapve se desarrollan aptitudes cognitivas, motrices, sociales y de conducta que resultan en ninos exitosos en la escuela y la vida

author: shakira
content: .@GuilleShak now I know that i'm my child’s first educator-spending time teaching him is so key since his brain is rapidly developing.

author: shakira
content: .@arneduncan Thank you for having me and taking the time to chat about an issue that’s close to both your heart & mine. Shak #ShakiraEdChat
